{"title":"New Cipollini Fybra GX e-Gravel Bike Adds HiRide AR Suspension w/ 18mm of Travel","link":"https://bikerumor.com/mario-cipollini-fybra-gx-e-gravel-bike/","date":1683143150000,"content":"<p>Cipollini… “Cipo” as we will refer to him for the rest of this press release, has been a controversial personality of the pro cycling circuit for the better part of two decades spanning from the late 80s to the early 2000s. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Super Mario was a force to be reckoned with during the last meters of any given Spring classic of the era. His light-hearted, albeit egotistical tomfoolery during his time at the top was sure fun to watch. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>What wasn’t fun to watch, was his womanizing, which we were reminded of lately, as Cipo was <a href=\"https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a41690004/mario-cipollini-sentenced-to-three-years-in-prison/\" target=\"_blank\">convicted of domestic abuse</a> in October 2022. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But, let’s talk about the bike I guess, since Mario Cipollini has now released an electric gravel bike in the new Fybra GX model.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Cipollini Fybra GX</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-dark-side-shot-e1683137826538.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"368\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-dark-side-shot-e1683137826538-800x368.jpeg\" alt=\"MCipollini Fybra GX dark side shot\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-dark-side-shot-e1683137826538-800x368.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-dark-side-shot-e1683137826538-297x136.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-dark-side-shot-e1683137826538-120x55.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-dark-side-shot-e1683137826538-768x353.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-dark-side-shot-e1683137826538.jpeg 1280w\" /></a><figcaption>Photo c. MCipollini Bicycles</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-front-side-e1683137924999.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"418\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-front-side-e1683137924999-800x418.jpeg\" alt=\"MCipollini Fybra GX front side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-front-side-e1683137924999-800x418.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-front-side-e1683137924999-297x155.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-front-side-e1683137924999-120x63.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-front-side-e1683137924999-768x401.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-front-side-e1683137924999.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-back-side-e1683137892881.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"412\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-back-side-e1683137892881-800x412.jpeg\" alt=\"MCipollini Fybra GX back side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-back-side-e1683137892881-800x412.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-back-side-e1683137892881-297x153.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-back-side-e1683137892881-120x62.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-back-side-e1683137892881-768x395.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-back-side-e1683137892881.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Fybra is the second electric bike in the collection following the Flusso. The Fybra comes in the GX variant (gravel) and the R (road), the 700c-designed GX version is the first electric gravel bike in the MCipollini line.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-22hidden22-GPS-locator.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-22hidden22-GPS-locator-800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"MCipollini Fybra GX hidden GPS locator\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-22hidden22-GPS-locator-800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-22hidden22-GPS-locator-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-22hidden22-GPS-locator-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-22hidden22-GPS-locator-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-22hidden22-GPS-locator-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-22hidden22-GPS-locator.jpeg 1280w\" /></a><figcaption>Shock adjustment nd “hidden” GPS locator.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>According to the press release, “Thanks to a HiRide AR 1.5 suspension, (horribly named, yet seems purposeful) integrated into the design with 18mm of travel, the bike allows for a spirited ride that winks at the MTB routes” (as it passes them?). </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-160mm-or-180mm-discs.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-160mm-or-180mm-discs-800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"MCipollini Fybra GX 160mm or 180mm discs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-160mm-or-180mm-discs-800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-160mm-or-180mm-discs-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-160mm-or-180mm-discs-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-160mm-or-180mm-discs-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-160mm-or-180mm-discs-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-160mm-or-180mm-discs.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The carbon fork on the Fybra GX is “optimized for specific off-road discs”. Those off-road sizes, according to MCipollini are the 160mm (widely used on all carbon gravel forks) and the 180mm, which they say “allows for safe braking in all situations”.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-wireless-dropper-e1683138238827.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"457\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-wireless-dropper-e1683138238827-800x457.jpeg\" alt=\"MCipollini Fybra GX wireless dropper\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-wireless-dropper-e1683138238827-800x457.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-wireless-dropper-e1683138238827-297x170.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-wireless-dropper-e1683138238827-120x69.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-wireless-dropper-e1683138238827-768x439.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-wireless-dropper-e1683138238827.jpeg 1276w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Fybra GX also comes with a wireless RockShox Reverb AX dropper post that can be operated from the shift levers. Both of the gravel GX and the road R models use the same monocoque frame with TCM technology “which allows for continuity in the carbon fibers”. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-R-Polini-motor.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-R-Polini-motor-800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"MCipollini Fybra R Polini motor\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-R-Polini-motor-800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-R-Polini-motor-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-R-Polini-motor-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-R-Polini-motor-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-R-Polini-motor-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-R-Polini-motor.jpeg 1280w\" /></a><figcaption>Fybra R with the same Polini motor as the Fybra GX.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Both models are equipped with the same Polini EP3+ EVO motor which they claim is at the top of its category in terms of “output quality”. The included power indicator and the display are color as well.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-Color-dispay.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-Color-dispay-800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"MCipollini Fybra GX Color display\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-Color-dispay-800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-Color-dispay-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-Color-dispay-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-Color-dispay-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-Color-dispay-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/MCipollini-Fybra-GX-Color-dispay.jpeg 1280w\" /></a><figcaption>Cockpit, color display, shock adjuster</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These bikes come with some theft protection built right in with the self-powered, integrated GPS locator that is ‘hidden’ in the frame. They both have integrated lights that are powered directly from the eBike. The Polini 500Wh battery boasts a “guaranteed long distance of up to 220km.”</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Fybra GX Specs, Geo, and Retail</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Specifications</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><table><tbody><tr></tr><tr><td>BOTTOM BRACKET</td><td>Isis</td></tr><tr><td>HEADSET</td><td>Specific headset (IS52/IS52)</td></tr><tr><td>SEATPOST</td><td>Offset 0mm; 140g (variante R30SS)</td></tr><tr><td>BRAKE SYSTEM</td><td>Disc brake (140/160 Rear Flat Mount, Thru Axle 12 x 142 mm – 160/180 Front Flat Mount, Thru Axle 12 x 100 mm)</td></tr><tr><td>FRAME WEIGHT</td><td>1.440g</td></tr><tr><td>FORK WEIGHT</td><td>426g (without suspension)</td></tr><tr><td>MAXIMUM TIRE</td><td>Max 50 mm (Measured Width) on 700cc – Recommended 47 mm (Measured Width) on 700cc</td></tr><tr><td>REAR CHAINSTAY HEIGHT CALIPER ATTACHMENT AREA</td><td>20 mm</td></tr><tr><td>WEIGHT GX RIVAL XPLR</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption>GE</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Geometry</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-e1683136779736.png\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-e1683136779736-800x490.png\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-e1683136779736-800x490.png 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-e1683136779736-297x182.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-e1683136779736-120x73.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-e1683136779736-768x470.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-e1683136779736-1536x940.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-e1683136779736.png 1572w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><table><thead><tr><th></th><th>A</th><th>A1</th><th>B</th><th>a<sup>°</sup></th><th>b<sup>°</sup></th><th>C</th><th>D</th><th>E</th><th>F</th><th>G</th><th>reach</th><th>stack</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>XS</td><td>434</td><td>595</td><td>530</td><td>73.5°</td><td>71.5°</td><td>126</td><td>55</td><td>588</td><td>4440</td><td>80</td><td>361</td><td>572</td></tr><tr><td>S</td><td>458</td><td>602</td><td>542</td><td>73.5°</td><td>71.5°</td><td>132</td><td>55</td><td>600</td><td>440</td><td>80</td><td>370</td><td>578</td></tr><tr><td>M</td><td>484</td><td>612</td><td>560</td><td>73.5°</td><td>72.5°</td><td>136</td><td>55</td><td>610</td><td>440</td><td>80</td><td>386</td><td>586</td></tr><tr><td>L</td><td>504</td><td>635</td><td>580</td><td>73.5°</td><td>72.5°</td><td>160</td><td>55</td><td>629</td><td>440</td><td>80</td><td>400</td><td>610</td></tr><tr><td>XL</td><td>526</td><td>662</td><td>600</td><td>73.5°</td><td>72.5°</td><td>186</td><td>55</td><td>650</td><td>440</td><td>77,5</td><td>412</td><td>635</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Fybra GX color is carbon, sand and green. The Fybra GX and R will be available through MCipollini dealers coming this June. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Retail</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: 14,700 € (SRAM Rival AXS XPLR)</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.mcipollini.com/\" target=\"_blank\">MCipollini.com</a></em></p>\n\n\n\n<p> </p>\n\n\n\n<p> </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/mario-cipollini-fybra-gx-e-gravel-bike/\">New Cipollini Fybra GX e-Gravel Bike Adds HiRide AR Suspension w/ 18mm of Travel</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"89c9f89b822eac41376f4a42deaae2b1aba809532a301ef9d23ba1e360f4ebcd","category":"Cycling"}